# Prevent the Docker build context from ballooning. The Dockerfile copies
# only the two project directories it actually needs, but .dockerignore
# still has to strip any large build artefacts the user may have left in
# those directories.

**/bin
**/obj
**/TestResults
**/artifacts
**/.vs
**/.vscode
**/.idea
**/.gh-pages-worktree
**/node_modules

# Never bake checkpoints or large gguf assets into a worker image.
**/Data/Models
**/*.gguf
**/*.bin.bak
**/*.checkpoint.json
**/*.bitnet.json
**/*.traditional.json

# Local zips and tarballs sometimes sit next to the source while we iterate.
**/*.zip
**/*.tar
**/*.tar.gz

# Source control and editor scratch.
.git
.gitignore
.github
.claude
.azuredevops

# Repository-level files that the build does not need.
README.md
LICENSE*
docs/
tests/
Directory.Packages.props
